snippet.textDisplay:
Can anyone confirm that the twilight wings is written by someone else who is not involved with the main series of pokemon involving Ash?
Because this is more mature, more realistic, more living world, continuity and consistency are deep concern eventhough it is 6 minutes. It really progressed more than Ash did in 20 seasons ie in a year eventhough there are more than thousand episodes and Ash is still 10.
I can't believe when they can do something like this, they stick stable with completely nonsensical, illogical stuff with Ash. Don't get me wrong I love Ash. But I hate BW and afterwards because everything was so invalid.
Cameron, Unova league, Ash reset, Ash age reset, mega-evolve that never used, z moves that never used, gigamax that is never going to be used ever after the region. So region locking features is a way to escape? Writers were lazy and incompetent. Kalos league was just 2 games... 2 games... 3 year waited for 2 games in one of which Ash loses big time for no reason. Alain? Why is that dude even there? Isn't he an heir to billion dollar company? didn't he conquer all the elite 4 and champions? Oh wait I need to defeat Ash because I haven't already done that 3 times before right?
And Alola compansation even worse than Orange League compansation!! Like no gyms, no full matches. no proper league at all! And still a champion which nobody even knows.
Bad executions!! Then abandone all the previous pokemons, if there is an ace pokemon like greninja, dump them so they may never return! Never develop your old team?? All the good trainers and champions always stick stable with a core team and strategy. Ash only seems to have a strategy of using agile pokemon.
Anyways, just this 6 minutes was better than whole Alola, Kalos, Unova combined period!
